<L>__{interior recovery chamber night}
<A>__{linda enters to find sebastian reading the collected works of t.s. elliot.}
<C>__{linda}
<D>__{want to talk about it?}
<C>__{sebastian}
<D>__{no.}
<A>__{linda looks over his shoulder.}
<C>__{linda}
<D>__{"we are the hollow men, the stuffed men, headpieces filled with straw."}
<C>__{sebastian}
<D>__{funny, huh? i've become a literal metaphor.}
<A>__{he puts the books down.}
<C>__{linda}
<D>__{i don't want to fight you. i just want what's best for the program.}
<C>__{sebastian}
<D>__{i know. and you being right doesn't make it any easier for me.}
<C>__{linda}
<D>__{you can be scared. that's okay.}
<C>__{sebastian}
<D>__{i'm not scared of being stuck this way. with a little more make up and practice, i could...}
<P>__{(he motions to his face)}
<D>__{... pass. y'know, get by in the world. but the testing...}
<C>__{linda}
<D>__{you're talking like you've given up. it's only been a few months.}
<C>__{sebastian}
<D>__{what if it's years? i don't know how much more testing i can take.}
